Doctor Who BBC Breakfast 040508 - Nick Briggs (Dalek Voice) &amp; James Strong

Here is one that hasn&amp;#039;t made proper rounds on the Internet yet.   Nick Briggs (of Big Finish Productions) whom is also the voice of the Daleks in the newest Doctor Who series, appeared with James Strong, one of the Directors of the new 4th series, on BBC Breakfast on April 5th 2008, right before the launch of season 4. 

Do enjoy.   


And here is one I am looking for, please.   Also, BBC Breakfast on April 25th or 26th of 2008, hosted an interview with Dick Mills and Mark Ayres, both of whom worked extensively on Doctor Who, with Ayres still being involved in the sound restoration for classic series DVD releases.  That Interview surrounded the 50th Anniversary of the Radiophonic Workshop, where Delia Derbyshire started out.   See here (look down to April 25th);
